{"submission_id":"sub_a9f48b8e64371107","run_id":"2026-06-19T17-54-14-829Z_357538-4f94614f_ingest_34th-st-curbside-activity","submitted_at":"2026-06-19T17:56:39.982Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:a9f48b8e64371107d88aca43b2da33c83e19b867bff443af6163205584e9df64","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"34th_st_curbside_activity","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_data_collection_methods","label":"Data collection methods","raw_text":"DOT reached out directly to building managers to discuss typical curbside activities and needs...Project staff also conducted field observations of curbside activities on 34th Street, 33rd Street and 35th Street, as well as along the adjoining avenues, and reviewed GPS data on taxi drop-offs and pick-ups along the corridor. In addition, DOT met with representatives of the trucking industry, including the New York State Motor Truck Association and the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, to discuss delivery practices on 34th Street.","payload":{"claim_text":"DOT reached out directly to building managers, conducted field observations of curbside activities on 34th Street, 33rd Street and 35th Street and adjoining avenues, reviewed GPS data on taxi drop-offs and pick-ups along the corridor, and met with representatives of the trucking industry including the New York State Motor Truck Association and the International Brotherhood of Teamsters.","description":"Methods used to gather curbside activity data beyond the Community Forums and survey"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"34th_st_curbside_activity","evidence_id":"34th_st_curbside_activity#p001_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/34th_st_curbside_activity/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:accbc917d9875900278f3af25dbb33933c28665810e2d160f093d6a4618a1e9a","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
